  "text": "The correlation function appearing above is the connected Euclidean correlation function on R 3 , and so we may drop the constant term in [CITATION_1] . To regulate this calculation, we have cut out a tubular neighborhood of radius a around the entangling surface by restricting the integration over x in equation (11) to the region τ 2 E + y 2 ≥ a 2 (Fig. 4) ; we will send a → 0 at the end of the calculation. Integrating by parts in x, we find",
